# OS keychain / Credential Manager naming

- **Service name** (keyring “service” / grouping for `findCredentials`): `ecp` — see `ECP_KEYRING_SERVICE` in `packages/extensions/secrets/src/constants.ts`.
- **Storage target** (per-secret): `ecp://<logical-key>` via `osKeychainCredentialTarget` / `secretRefIdFromLogicalKey`, created with `Entry.withTarget(target, ECP_KEYRING_SERVICE, username)` so Windows does not synthesize `username.service` targets like `ecp.KEY.ecp`.
- **Username** field passed to the keyring is the canonical logical key (`canonicalSecretKeyForOsStorage`: trim, `\` → `/`).
- **`normalizeOsKeychainAccountKey`** remains for dotted `ecp.*` legacy helpers only; do not use it for store / load / delete on `OsKeychainSecretsStore`.
- **`list`** maps OS `account` strings to logical keys (handles either logical usernames or full `ecp://…` targets).
